OL,3,C'Outright thuggery': Political leaders
OL,4,Ccondemn Belfast riots as homes set
OL,5,Calight
OL,7,FGood Morning Britain's Senior
OL,8,FCorrespondent Jonathan Swain reports
OL,9,Ffrom the streets of Belfast after a
OL,10,Fnight of violent unrest on the
OL,11,Fstreets; with Political Correspondent
OL,12,FLouisa James from Westminster
OL,14,FNorthern Ireland's First Minister
OL,15,FMichelle O'Neill condemned the
OL,16,F"outright thuggery" that swept parts
OL,17,Fof Belfast as rioters took to the
OL,18,Fstreets in response to a knife attack.
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/17
