OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781165113
OL,3,C'Outright thuggery': Political leaders
OL,4,Ccondemn Belfast riots as homes set
OL,5,Calight
OL,7,FDeputy First Minister Emma Little-
OL,8,FPengelly said: "Taking frustration at
OL,9,Fthe evil actions of a person out on
OL,10,Fthose who had no part in it is utterly
OL,11,Fwrong."
OL,13,FShe said that violence does not
OL,14,F"advance any cause, it damages it",
OL,15,Fadding: "Destroying things within your
OL,16,Fown community benefits no one.
OL,26,@pD@POUsD@GO]vD@AOUvD@bO]wD@IOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781165113
OL,3,C'Outright thuggery': Political leaders
OL,4,Ccondemn Belfast riots as homes set
OL,5,Calight
OL,7,F"Engaging in violence risks your own
OL,8,Fsafety, that of others and
OL,9,Ffundamentally does any cause or
OL,10,Fcampaign to be heard terrible
OL,11,Fdisservice and damage."
OL,13,FCondemning those who have ignored
OL,14,Fcalls for calm, Northern Ireland's
OL,15,FJustice Minister Naomi Long said:
OL,16,F"They are intent on wreaking
OL,17,Fdestruction on the very communities
OL,18,Fthey claim they are trying to protect.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@WO]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781165113
OL,3,C'Outright thuggery': Political leaders
OL,4,Ccondemn Belfast riots as homes set
OL,5,Calight
OL,7,F"They are weaponising the genuine
OL,8,Fhurt, concern and anger that people
OL,9,Fare feeling for their own misguided
OL,10,Fpurposes.
OL,12,F"There is no place for masked thugs to
OL,13,Ftake to the streets and threaten,
OL,14,Fintimidate, disrupt and cause wanton
OL,15,Fdamage ` it is simply disingenuous to
OL,16,Fclaim this is being carried out for
OL,17,Fthe good of Northern Ireland."
OL,19,FShe added: "I would appeal once again
OL,20,Fto communities not to allow themselves
OL,21,Fto be used and abused in this manner.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUyD@^O]{D@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781165113
OL,3,C'Outright thuggery': Political leaders
OL,4,Ccondemn Belfast riots as homes set
OL,5,Calight
OL,7,F"Disorder on the streets, such as we
OL,8,Fare seeing tonight, is diverting
OL,9,Fvaluable police resources away from
OL,10,Fthose who genuinely need them.
OL,12,F"These are not the actions of people
OL,13,Fwho genuinely care about their
OL,14,Fcommunities. While I recognise and
OL,15,Funderstand the concerns following on
OL,16,Ffrom the attack in north Belfast, hate
OL,17,Fcannot be allowed to win."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUyD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/17
