OL,3,C'Outright thuggery': Political leaders
OL,4,Ccondemn Belfast riots as homes set
OL,5,Calight
OL,7,FThe UK government's Northern Ireland
OL,8,FSecretary Hilary Benn said: "The
OL,9,Fscenes of disorder we have witnessed
OL,10,Fin some parts of Northern Ireland this
OL,11,Fevening are only damaging communities
OL,12,Fand putting innocent lives at risk.
OL,14,F"There is no justification at all for
OL,15,Fthis type of destruction and thuggery."
OL,17,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer said:
OL,18,F"The horrific attack in Belfast last
OL,19,Fnight is sickening. I have absolutely
OL,20,Fno tolerance for abhorrent scenes of
OL,21,Fviolence like this on our streets.
OL,26,@pD@]OUvD@AOUwD@gO]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
